   "body" : "After some discussion with @jonasschnelli, I've put together a few notes about increasing our minimum supported version of macOS.\r\n\r\nOur current minimum is [10.8](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/depends/hosts/darwin.mk#L1).\r\nWe're using the 10.11 [SDK](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/depends/hosts/darwin.mk#L2).\r\n\r\nThere's currently #12971 open to upgrade Qt in depends to 5.9.x (up from 5.7.1). Starting with Qt 5.9.x the minimum supported version of macOS is [10.10](https://wiki.qt.io/Qt_5.9_Tools_and_Versions#osx_10.10_x86_64).\r\n\r\nTargeting 10.10+ should allow us to remove some macOS specific backwards compatibility code as well:\r\n* Font substitution in [guiutil.cpp](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/src/qt/guiutil.cpp#L420).\r\n* Weak linking in [macnotificationhandler.mm](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/src/qt/macnotificationhandler.mm#L36). Note this could probably be dropped already, due to 10.8+.\r\n\r\n@theuni be good to get your thoughts re Clang, cctools, macOS SDK etc.\r\n\r\nTagged with a 0.17.0 milestone, as if we plan to upgrade Qt in depends, this will need addressing somehow.",
